																		.roll 4df
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1618170&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250833" alt="Jack Ike" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1618170)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;" >Jack Ike</a></span> <span class="odate time_1463901612 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 May 2016 07:20</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2512720">
									

<p>5 hours to write first draft, about an hour to clean up issues brought up in reviews. Then it came here. Thanks to the following for reviewing:</p>
<ul>
<li>AidenEldritch</li>
<li>WrongJohnSilver</li>
<li>NinjaPhoenix</li>
<li>Fausto</li>
<li>OZ Ouroboros</li>
<li><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">That antimeme</span></li>
</ul>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Items&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;tale</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;lel&nbsp;ZK-Class&nbsp;first&nbsp;aid&nbsp;kit.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><a href="/scp-458">The Pizza Box - SCP-458</a><br />
<a href="/scp-109">The Water Canteen - SCP-109</a><br />
The Machine - Scranton Reality Anchor<br />
Listed Groups - Some of the GOI's<br />
The Entity - ???<br />
<span style="color:#ffffff">The red off button - SCP-001-J</span><br />
The story that the entity recalls is the <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Keys_to_the_Kingdom">//Keys to the Kingdom//</a> series by Garth Nix - specifically, the final book <em>Lord Sunday</em>. (It's a good series. You should read it.)</p>
</div>
</div>
