    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2513000">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2513000">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2513000)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2513000">
																		Re: .roll 4df
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250833" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1463957357 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 May 2016 22:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2513000">
									

<p>I am not sure that there's any evidence that reality anchors are especially effective at preserving much more than information between realities (other than perhaps the weapon system on the <em>Solidarity</em> but even that might actually be about preserving velocity and charge of the penetrators on the quantum level). All (or nearly all) uses in SCP articles are really just a narrative device to show multiple realities in a single document.</p>
<p>Also what is the connection to <em>Fudge</em><em>/Fate</em>?</p>

							</div>

								
					
