    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2513006">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2513006">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2513006)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2513006">
																		Re: .roll 4df
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1618170&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250833" alt="Jack Ike" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1618170)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-ike" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1618170); return false;" >Jack Ike</a></span> <span class="odate time_1463959075 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 May 2016 23:17</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2513006">
									

<p>Every time i've uploaded a skip or tale, I've had the first respons titled with a reference to dice/chance of some sort - a reference to &quot;Alea iacta est&quot;, in that since i've no uploaded the skip/tale I have no control over how well it will do.</p>
<p>Though the fact &quot;Alea iacta est&quot; is used to indicate when things have passed a point from which they cannot return is also rather convenient considering the context of the tale.</p>

							</div>

								
							<div class="changes">
