						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2623921)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2623921">
																		Endings
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1359534"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1474003402 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Sep 2016 05:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2623921">
									

<p>The gradual reality failure in Rat's Nest is a creative thing as much as a destructive thing. I don't really see existence ending, just existence as we know it ending. As much as I like this tale, it's just another idea in an open canon.</p>

